            <div class="wcutext">
                Through containerization with Docker, I learned how to create reproducible environments that eliminate the “it works on my machine” problem. This hands-on experience gave me a stronger understanding of how applications are tested, deployed, and maintained with consistency across local and cloud systems.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
            <h4 class="wcuheader">From Code to Cloud</h4>
            <div class="wcutext">
                The journey from writing code to deploying a working product in the cloud taught me how interconnected every stage of DevOps is. I used the Azure Portal to deploy, monitor, and scale applications—connecting the dots between development and operations while gaining valuable experience in cloud-based management.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
            <h4 class="wcuheader">Continuous Learning</h4>
            <div class="wcutext">
                DevOps isn’t just a set of tools—it’s a mindset of continuous improvement. Each project challenged me to streamline processes, adopt automation, and reflect on how to deliver better, faster, and more reliably. This approach mirrors what’s expected in real-world DevOps teams, where learning never stops.
